Inkternity is a fork of InfiniPaint by Yousef Khadadeh
(https://github.com/ErrorAtLine0/infinipaint). The code inherited
from InfiniPaint was received under the MIT License; its verbatim
text and Yousef Khadadeh's copyright notice are preserved at
`assets/data/third_party_licenses/InfiniPaint/LICENSE.txt`. The MIT
grant remains in effect perpetually for the portions of Inkternity
that originate from InfiniPaint.

Inkternity as a whole is distributed under BUSL-1.1 — see the
`LICENSE` file at the repository root for terms, change-date, and
change-license.

Upstream InfiniPaint relicensed its master branch from MIT to
GPL-3.0 on 2026-05-11 (upstream commit `fc8f414`). Inkternity's
fork point predates that relicense (last shared upstream commit:
`8b3e321`), so Inkternity carries only MIT-era code from upstream
and no GPL-3.0 obligation. Any future upstream commits Inkternity
chooses to incorporate must either predate 2026-05-11 or be
relicensed separately; the BUSL-1.1 / GPL-3.0 incompatibility
blocks any direct merge of post-relicense upstream changes.

Third-party libraries are used in this project. The licenses for
these libraries are included in `assets/data/third_party_licenses`.
That directory includes licenses for direct dependencies as well
as for some of the dependencies of libraries used by this project.
